01:35:52,543 --> 01:35:53,709
all right, cowboy.

1525
01:35:53,710 --> 01:35:55,778
claim second money.
come on.

1526
01:35:55,779 --> 01:35:57,013
I told you once before.

1527
01:35:57,014 --> 01:35:59,948
stop sticking your nose
in my business.

1528
01:36:01,384 --> 01:36:04,418
well, I picked him real
slow and real careful.

1529
01:36:04,554 --> 01:36:07,421
I got married
for a home. I got one.

1530
01:36:07,590 --> 01:36:09,658
I wanted to get away
from working...

1531
01:36:09,659 --> 01:36:11,760
he just kissed
a little blonde.

1532
01:36:11,761 --> 01:36:12,761
it don't mean anything.

1533
01:36:12,762 --> 01:36:14,663
it won't look so terrible
tomorrow morning.

1534
01:36:14,664 --> 01:36:17,199
I wouldn't see him
tomorrow morning or any morning.

1535
01:36:17,200 --> 01:36:20,335
when he sobers up,
he'll say, "honey, I'm sorry,"

1536
01:36:21,203 --> 01:36:22,804
and you'll forgive him.

1537
01:36:22,805 --> 01:36:23,672
I won't.

1538
01:36:23,673 --> 01:36:24,438
sure, you will.

1539
01:36:24,439 --> 01:36:27,342
that's a wife's profession...
forgiving her husband.

1540
01:36:27,343 --> 01:36:29,510
please help me.

1541
01:36:30,212 --> 01:36:33,246
get him away from here.
it's his only chance.

1542
01:36:33,649 --> 01:36:34,849
it's my only chance.

1543
01:36:34,850 --> 01:36:37,985
he puts on his own pants.
he buttons his own shirt.

1544
01:36:38,654 --> 01:36:41,621
if he does that,
he can run his own life.

1545
01:36:42,257 --> 01:36:43,023
but he doesn't.

1546
01:36:43,924 --> 01:36:47,025
either you beat the money,
or the money beats you.

1547
01:36:47,962 --> 01:36:50,896
that's all
you care about... the money.

1548
01:36:51,065 --> 01:36:52,465
when you're
finished with Wes,

1549
01:36:52,466 --> 01:36:54,801
you'll get yourself
another cowhand.

1550
01:36:54,802 --> 01:36:56,736
you're only thinking
of the money.

1551
01:36:56,737 --> 01:36:59,438
just a minute.
let me tell you something.

1552
01:36:59,439 --> 01:37:02,307
when Wes asked me
to come into this,

1553
01:37:02,375 --> 01:37:03,442
maybe I told myself

1554
01:37:03,443 --> 01:37:06,311
that the money
was making up my mind,

1555
01:37:06,480 --> 01:37:07,346
but it wasn't.

1556
01:37:07,347 --> 01:37:08,547
I was lying to myself.

1557
01:37:08,548 --> 01:37:11,716
the only thing that kept me
stringing along was you.

1558
01:37:13,886 --> 01:37:15,320
hope's a funny thing.

1559
01:37:15,321 --> 01:37:16,555
you can have it

1560
01:37:16,556 --> 01:37:19,424
even though there
ain't no reason for it.

1561
01:37:19,425 --> 01:37:22,359
you can tell me
to shut up and move on,

1562
01:37:22,962 --> 01:37:24,296
like anybody
at your door

1563
01:37:24,297 --> 01:37:27,132
trying to sell you
something you don't want.

1564
01:37:27,133 --> 01:37:28,566
I'm just
waiting to hear

1565
01:37:28,567 --> 01:37:31,535
what the lady
of the house has to say.

1566
01:37:38,944 --> 01:37:41,812
don't let Wes end up
the way you did.

1567
01:37:42,981 --> 01:37:45,949
you mean a washed-up,
beat-up bronc rider.

1568
01:37:46,651 --> 01:37:48,085
I didn't mean that.

1569
01:37:48,086 --> 01:37:49,520
all I meant was...

1570
01:37:49,521 --> 01:37:52,322
don't let him
wind up crippled.

1571
01:37:52,824 --> 01:37:55,991
that's all you
really care about is Wes, isn't it?

1572
01:38:05,069 --> 01:38:08,038
it's funny
how the people you never figure

1573
01:38:08,039 --> 01:38:09,739
ought to be together
always are.

1574
01:38:09,740 --> 01:38:12,842
all right, mrs. Merritt,
I'll go back and tell him.

1575
01:38:13,845 --> 01:38:16,812
I made my pitch.
the lady just didn't buy.

1576
01:38:16,813 --> 01:38:19,848
we'll come back here
after we close the joint.

1577
01:38:23,253 --> 01:38:26,088
I do think I ought
to kiss you just once

1578
01:38:26,089 --> 01:38:28,790
for all the times
I won't.

1579
01:38:33,730 --> 01:38:35,297
ain't that pretty,

1580
01:38:35,298 --> 01:38:38,266
out here in the corridor
playing post office?

1581
01:38:38,267 --> 01:38:40,869
somebody's going
to get real fed up with you

1582
01:38:40,870 --> 01:38:43,838
and beat your
head in with a rake handle.

1583
01:38:43,839 --> 01:38:44,873
your friend?

1584
01:38:45,375 --> 01:38:47,742
be the first thing
you've done on your own

1585
01:38:47,743 --> 01:38:48,710
since I knew you.

1586
01:38:48,711 --> 01:38:51,646
you've just been dragging
your foot in my stirrup.

1587
01:38:51,647 --> 01:38:53,181
you got
anything to say,

1588
01:38:53,182 --> 01:38:54,281
say it
at the stables.

1589
01:38:54,282 --> 01:38:56,718
playing me for a sucker.
taking half my dough.

1590
01:38:56,719 --> 01:38:59,653
why? because
you ain't got guts to ride yourself.

1591
01:38:59,654 --> 01:39:02,923
all that fancy talk
about being through with rodeoeoing.

1592
01:39:03,658 --> 01:39:04,658
you'll never be through

1593
01:39:04,659 --> 01:39:07,395
as long as you ride
somebody else's shoulders.

1594
01:39:07,396 --> 01:39:08,028
you're yellow!

1595
01:39:08,029 --> 01:39:11,063
you ain't got guts enough
to ride a dead mule.

1596
01:39:14,636 --> 01:39:17,203
you bounce real good.

1597
01:39:22,711 --> 01:39:25,745
bronc riders.
I never met a bronc rider yet

1598
01:39:25,746 --> 01:39:27,647
that wasn't
a wild man.

1599
01:39:27,648 --> 01:39:29,682
but if they
weren't wild men,

1600
01:39:29,683 --> 01:39:31,418
they wouldn't
be bronc riders.

1601
01:39:31,419 --> 01:39:33,885
you still sure?

1602
01:39:35,021 --> 01:39:37,523
ginny, you keep an eye
on mrs. Merritt.

1603
01:39:37,524 --> 01:39:40,426
she'll need a place
to sleep tonight.

1604
01:39:42,496 --> 01:39:45,497
remember once a party
in butte, montana.

1605
01:39:45,531 --> 01:39:46,132
big hotel.

1606
01:39:46,133 --> 01:39:48,901
fella's wife
kissed another fella,

1607
01:39:48,902 --> 01:39:51,402
and this fella...

1608
01:40:05,251 --> 01:40:07,285
once again,
it's my pleasure

1609
01:40:07,286 --> 01:40:08,186
to describe to you

1610
01:40:08,187 --> 01:40:10,756
an outstanding event
in the world of sports...

1611
01:40:10,757 --> 01:40:12,323
the annual
pendleton roundup.

1612
01:40:12,324 --> 01:40:13,591
passing before us now,

1613
01:40:13,592 --> 01:40:15,927
an exciting display
of old glory,

1614
01:40:15,928 --> 01:40:18,663
followed by our friends
the yumatella indians.

1615
01:40:18,664 --> 01:40:20,465
adding more color
to this review,

1616
01:40:20,466 --> 01:40:23,268
the serpentine ride
by the cowboy contestants

1617
01:40:23,269 --> 01:40:25,102
in the center
of the arena.

1618
01:40:42,853 --> 01:40:44,788
what do you say,
bobby?

1619
01:40:44,789 --> 01:40:46,423
you sweetening up
the kitty?

1620
01:40:46,424 --> 01:40:47,791
get off his back.

1621
01:40:47,792 --> 01:40:49,326
you might ride
for second.

1622
01:40:49,327 --> 01:40:51,927
well, I'm just kidding.

1623
01:40:56,200 --> 01:40:58,400
what do you think
you're doing?

1624
01:40:58,401 --> 01:41:00,003
what's it look like?

1625
01:41:00,004 --> 01:41:01,137
signing up, huh?

1626
01:41:01,138 --> 01:41:03,807
calf roping, steer
tying, bulldogging,

1627
01:41:03,808 --> 01:41:04,673
bareback,
and saddle bronc.

1628
01:41:04,674 --> 01:41:07,608
everything
but ladies' trick riding.

1629
01:41:08,845 --> 01:41:11,380
I owe you
$350 entry fee.

1630
01:41:11,381 --> 01:41:12,215
just a minute, Jeff.

1631
01:41:12,216 --> 01:41:15,416
you letting
this ruckus with Wes get under your skin.

1632
01:41:16,118 --> 01:41:17,386
that's my business,
gentlemen.

1633
01:41:17,387 --> 01:41:18,454
let's talk this over.

1634
01:41:18,455 --> 01:41:21,622
take that money
and hand me one of those numbers.

1635
01:41:34,337 --> 01:41:36,003
you out
of your head?

1636
01:41:36,004 --> 01:41:37,672
you ain't
rodeoed all season.

1637
01:41:37,673 --> 01:41:39,640
you're
in no condition to compete.

1638
01:41:39,641 --> 01:41:42,443
the only thing
you've got to worry about

1639
01:41:42,444 --> 01:41:45,211
is keeping
those chutes loaded.

1640
01:42:17,677 --> 01:42:19,913
wouldn't let
nobody use them but you.

1641
01:42:19,914 --> 01:42:22,848
won the average
four years at calgary with them.

1642
01:42:22,849 --> 01:42:26,051
set a record
they been shooting at for 20 years...9.3.

1643
01:42:27,187 --> 01:42:29,555
I'll be satisfied
with 14 flat.

1644
01:42:29,556 --> 01:42:32,024
I hear you've signed up
for four events.

1645
01:42:32,025 --> 01:42:34,527
quit yapping.
ain't nobody in your class.

1646
01:42:34,528 --> 01:42:37,195
now we're going to see
some records broke.

1647
01:42:37,196 --> 01:42:39,564
but you ain't
competed all year.

1648
01:42:39,565 --> 01:42:42,499
honey, I got told
two things yesterday.

1649
01:42:43,736 --> 01:42:47,004
one was to keep my nose
out of other people's business.

1650
01:42:47,573 --> 01:42:50,507
that's pretty good advice
all around.

1651
01:43:01,854 --> 01:43:03,121
our first contestant
in calf roping

1652
01:43:03,122 --> 01:43:05,824
will be Jeff mccloud
of bandera, texas.

1653
01:43:05,825 --> 01:43:06,958
Jeff's making
his first appearance

1654
01:43:06,959 --> 01:43:09,961
after a year's layoff
because of a leg injury.

1655
01:43:09,962 --> 01:43:12,963
I'm sure rodeo contestants
and rodeo fans alike

1656
01:43:12,964 --> 01:43:16,166
are happy to welcome Jeff
back to competition.

1657
01:43:32,183 --> 01:43:34,217
guess he's
a little overanxious,

1658
01:43:34,218 --> 01:43:37,319
but he's going to try
for a second throw.

1659
01:43:59,942 --> 01:44:01,943
you're going away.

1660
01:44:01,944 --> 01:44:03,812
because of Wes?

1661
01:44:03,813 --> 01:44:05,814
no, honey,
because of me.

1662
01:44:05,815 --> 01:44:07,916
did you hear about Jeff?

1663
01:44:07,917 --> 01:44:09,485
no. did he leave?

1664
01:44:09,486 --> 01:44:10,819
I wish he had.

1665
01:44:10,820 --> 01:44:12,286
he's going
to rodeo today.

1666
01:44:12,287 --> 01:44:13,955
he signed up
for four events.

1667
01:44:13,956 --> 01:44:16,758
no matter
what booker says, he ain't in shape.

1668
01:44:16,759 --> 01:44:18,592
everybody knows it
but Jeff.

1669
01:44:18,593 --> 01:44:21,594
they say
he's just doing it to show Wes.

1670
01:44:23,332 --> 01:44:24,965
no, that isn't it.

1671
01:44:24,966 --> 01:44:27,934
maybe it's because
he needs the day money.

1672
01:44:28,637 --> 01:44:31,271
that isn't it,
either.

1673
01:44:31,473 --> 01:44:32,840
where is he?

1674
01:44:32,841 --> 01:44:34,742
over at the chutes.

1675
01:44:34,743 --> 01:44:37,744
Wes Merritt
of big springs, texas.

1676
01:44:51,059 --> 01:44:54,126
the time for Wes Merritt
is 21.4 seconds.

1677
01:44:54,895 --> 01:44:58,096
it looks like Jeff mccloud
is going all the way.

1678
01:44:58,265 --> 01:45:01,132
he's next up
in bulldogging,

1679
01:45:01,168 --> 01:45:03,402
and he's chosen
for his hazer

1680
01:45:03,403 --> 01:45:04,570
a lifelong friend

1681
01:45:04,571 --> 01:45:07,639
and old-time rodeo great
of past years,

1682
01:45:08,008 --> 01:45:09,242
booker davis.

1683
01:45:09,243 --> 01:45:10,309
man be in trouble

1684
01:45:10,310 --> 01:45:12,178
if he front-holds
a steer this big.

1685
01:45:12,179 --> 01:45:15,180
I reckon I'll throw him
with a half nelson.

1686
01:45:15,315 --> 01:45:18,083
have him in shape
to throw him right.

1687
01:45:18,084 --> 01:45:21,085
if I have to,
I'll bump him in your lap.

1688
01:45:37,303 --> 01:45:40,170
Jeff's time...
11.6 seconds.

1689
01:45:44,142 --> 01:45:46,176
sure bedded him down
in a hurry.

1690
01:45:46,177 --> 01:45:48,546
that's good enough
for day money.

1691
01:45:48,547 --> 01:45:51,482
you had him in there
all the way for me.

1692
01:45:52,618 --> 01:45:53,550
to the chutes now

1693
01:45:53,551 --> 01:45:54,719
for the saddle bronc
riding.

1694
01:45:54,720 --> 01:45:55,686
our first contestant,

1695
01:45:55,687 --> 01:45:58,687
bob elliott
of newhall, california.

1696
01:46:04,062 --> 01:46:05,895
next out, Wes Merritt.

1697
01:46:05,896 --> 01:46:07,130
Wes will try his hand

1698
01:46:07,131 --> 01:46:10,333
on one of al dawson's
top broncs...black widow.

1699
01:46:29,320 --> 01:46:31,053
over to chute 8,
where Pete fox

1700
01:46:31,054 --> 01:46:32,688
from rapid city,
south dakota,

1701
01:46:32,689 --> 01:46:35,557
is coming out
on war paint.

1702
01:46:40,564 --> 01:46:41,697
looks like war paint

1703
01:46:41,698 --> 01:46:43,932
is really
on the warpath today.

1704
01:46:43,933 --> 01:46:46,500
tough break, Pete.

1705
01:46:50,439 --> 01:46:53,574
I think red
just stayed out too late last night.

1706
01:46:54,710 --> 01:46:57,345
oh, he did
pretty good.

1707
01:46:57,480 --> 01:47:00,314
hear you entered in
the saddle bronc riding.

1708
01:47:00,315 --> 01:47:01,783
well, you heard right.

1709
01:47:01,784 --> 01:47:03,451
picked a tough horse.

1710
01:47:03,452 --> 01:47:06,320
I remember saying
the same thing to Wes.

1711
01:47:06,321 --> 01:47:08,122
I can handle
anything he can.

1712
01:47:08,123 --> 01:47:11,091
everybody knows Wes
ain't in your class.

1713
01:47:11,593 --> 01:47:12,894
everybody but me.

1714
01:47:12,895 --> 01:47:13,928
now to chute number 6,

1715
01:47:13,929 --> 01:47:15,762
where Jeff mccloud
of bandera, texas,

1716
01:47:15,763 --> 01:47:18,432
the former saddle bronc
champion of the world,

1717
01:47:18,433 --> 01:47:21,601
will come out on a horse
called lightning rod.

1718
01:47:40,821 --> 01:47:43,389
all right. let me out.

1719
01:47:56,670 --> 01:47:59,004
look at that cowboy stick!

1720
01:47:59,005 --> 01:48:01,505
a great ride.

1721
01:48:05,011 --> 01:48:06,412
he's the best.

1722
01:48:06,413 --> 01:48:08,946
he's much of a man.

1723
01:48:10,350 --> 01:48:11,217
our pickup men

1724
01:48:11,218 --> 01:48:14,352
seem to be having trouble
getting to Jeff.

1725
01:48:15,488 --> 01:48:17,656
Jeff mccloud
is in trouble.

1726
01:48:20,325 --> 01:48:23,460
and he's got his foot
caught in the stirrup.

1727
01:48:43,014 --> 01:48:46,282
at chute 2, craig bentley
of salinas, california,

1728
01:48:46,550 --> 01:48:49,452
is coming out
on the drifter.

1729
01:49:01,865 --> 01:49:03,866
in here, boys.

1730
01:49:03,867 --> 01:49:05,401
out of chute number 2,

1731
01:49:05,402 --> 01:49:08,369
Wes Merritt,
big springs, texas.

1732
01:49:14,778 --> 01:49:17,578
come on, Wes.
you're next out.

1733
01:49:35,464 --> 01:49:38,232
what were you
trying to prove?

1734
01:49:43,305 --> 01:49:45,540
I used to make
my own money.

1735
01:49:45,541 --> 01:49:48,542
I used buy my own whiskey,
take my own falls.

1736
01:49:49,978 --> 01:49:53,046
a fella just likes to know
if he can still do it.

1737
01:49:55,050 --> 01:49:58,051
isn't one man enough
for you to worry about?

1738
01:49:58,987 --> 01:50:00,821
he ain't bad hurt.

1739
01:50:00,822 --> 01:50:02,622
he's showing
how tough he is.

1740
01:50:02,623 --> 01:50:04,892
broken rib. that's nothing.
I remember...

1741
01:50:04,893 --> 01:50:06,527
I told you
to lay still.

1742
01:50:07,695 --> 01:50:10,629
that rib's
sticking through his lung.

1743
01:50:12,132 --> 01:50:15,133
you're nothing
but a no-good, washed-out,

1744
01:50:15,470 --> 01:50:17,136
beat-up bronc rider.

1745
01:50:17,137 --> 01:50:19,972
all you know is
how to bust a gut.

1746
01:50:20,407 --> 01:50:21,941
the more bones
you break,

1747
01:50:21,942 --> 01:50:24,744
the bigger man
you think you are.

1748
01:50:34,020 --> 01:50:37,155
broken bones,
broken bottles, broken everything.

1749
01:50:38,358 --> 01:50:41,393
there never was a bronc
that couldn't be rode.

1750
01:50:42,996 --> 01:50:46,097
there never was a cowboy
that couldn't be throwed.

1751
01:50:46,900 --> 01:50:49,600
guys like me
last forever.

1752
01:51:23,901 --> 01:51:26,336
where's Jeff?

1753
01:51:27,071 --> 01:51:29,439
he's dead.

1754
01:51:35,847 --> 01:51:38,214
Wes Merritt
of big springs, texas,

1755
01:51:38,215 --> 01:51:40,350
coming out
of chute number 3

1756
01:51:40,351 --> 01:51:42,085
on a horse
called meditation.

1757
01:51:42,086 --> 01:51:44,586
pass Wes Merritt!

1758
01:52:01,905 --> 01:52:04,939
you couldn't use
two extra hands, could you?

1759
01:52:11,614 --> 01:52:14,015
sure, booker.

1760
01:52:15,017 --> 01:52:17,985
rusty, me and you
is going back to texas.

1761
01:52:18,788 --> 01:52:20,489
now our next rider,

1762
01:52:20,490 --> 01:52:22,390
rocky davis
from austin, nevada,

1763
01:52:22,391 --> 01:52:24,025
coming out on quicksand.

1764
01:52:24,026 --> 01:52:27,194
this is rocky davis'
first time on the circuit,

1765
01:52:27,262 --> 01:52:30,197
so let's give him
a warm welcome

1766
01:52:30,366 --> 01:52:31,799
with a big hand.

